{
  "stem": "22660.1",
  "chunk_idx": 11,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And my mother went in to the office of the head of the Gestapo in Hamburg.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And I don't know how long she was in there. 15 minutes, 20 minutes, half an hour, I don't know.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "It seemed a long time to us.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "We were waiting outside, my brother and I.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And my mother came out of that office drenched, just tears, and drenched.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And she had this little piece of paper, kind of rumpled in her hand.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And she said, come on, let's go.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "I got the permit.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And with that, we then went to the hospital, and we had to get my father discharged and packed our suitcases-- still ran downtown to get a couple of more new dresses.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "But in reality, just with one suitcase-- my parents, as I told you at the beginning of this interview, were travellers.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And they were very-- on very good terms with the management of Hamburg Sud, which is still a large company, bought ships.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And somehow or other, we did get on the [GERMAN], 11, 12 o'clock at night.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And that was the story that I'll just never forget, with my four grandparents sitting there-- standing there, not sitting there.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "Standing there at the harbor in Hamburg.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And that was horrible, horrible, horrible.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "OK, fine.",
      "word_count": 2
    }
  ],
